msgctxt "an4.73:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.73:0.2"
msgid "8. Apaṇṇakavagga "
msgstr "8. Guaranteed "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: asappurisavadhukāsuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.73:0.3"
msgid "73. Sappurisasutta "
msgstr "73. A Good Person "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.73:1.1"
msgid "“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato asappuriso veditabbo. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a bad person can be known by four qualities. "

msgctxt "an4.73:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.73:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, asappuriso yo hoti parassa avaṇṇo taṃ apuṭṭhopi pātu karoti, ko pana vādo puṭṭhassa. "
msgstr "To start with, a bad person speaks ill of another even when not asked, let alone when asked. "

msgctxt "an4.73:1.4"
msgid "Puṭṭho kho pana pañhābhinīto ahāpetvā alambitvā paripūraṃ vitthārena parassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitā hoti. "
msgstr "But when led on by questions they speak ill of another in full detail, not leaving anything out. "

msgctxt "an4.73:1.5"
msgid "Veditabbametaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso ayaṃ bhavanti. "
msgstr "That’s how to know that this is a bad person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.73:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, asappuriso yo hoti parassa vaṇṇo taṃ puṭṭhopi na pātu karoti, ko pana vādo apuṭṭhassa. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a bad person doesn’t speak well of another even when asked, let alone when not asked. "

